From 2ccd87bc141fefe8b1270a874b21c695018be6eb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mahesh Vaidya <mahesh.vaidya@altera.com>
Date: Sun, 15 Mar 2026 23:31:54 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: intel: agilex5: Add reserved memory for PCIe MSI
 ordering

Reserve a 4 KiB HPS memory region for the FPGA-based PCIe Root Port
hardware.

The Root Port design uses this buffer to handle MSI ordering by ensuring
that data written from the FPGA side has reached HPS memory before the
MSI interrupt is generated.

Mark the region no-map so the memory is not mapped or allocated by
Linux.

Upstream-Status: Pending [Will be submitted soon]
Signed-off-by: Mahesh Vaidya <mahesh.vaidya@altera.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/intel/socfpga_agilex5.dtsi | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/intel/socfpga_agilex5.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/intel/socfpga_agilex5.dtsi
index f2a2bc62878f..3b5ed2fd39d9 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/intel/socfpga_agilex5.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/intel/socfpga_agilex5.dtsi
@@ -26,6 +26,11 @@ service_reserved: svcbuffer@0 {
 			alignment = <0x1000>;
 			no-map;
 		};
+
+		pcie_rootport_buf: pcie-rootport-buf@9fffff000 {
+			reg = <0x00000009 0xfffff000 0x0 0x1000>;
+			no-map;
+		};
 	};
 
 	cpus {
-- 
